# Document 04 — UI/UX Design Brief

Visual language so the UI is consistent, not generic.

## Required sections

- Aesthetic direction (minimal, bold, corporate, etc.)
- Color palette: primary, background, text, accent/CTA
- Typography: fonts, heading/body sizes
- Component style: border radius, shadows, flat vs elevated
- Dark/light mode preference
- Reference apps (e.g. Linear, Notion)
- Key UI patterns (cards, tables, modals)
- Mobile responsiveness rules
- Accessibility (contrast, font size)

## Agent rules

- Store colors in the project colors file; font sizes in the design tokens file.
- All user-facing text goes in i18n/arb files (English + French when applicable).
- Match the brief across every screen — no one-off styling without approval.
